explain how django rest framework authentication and authorization  can be override

If we want to write our own authentication and authorization we can override django built   classes 

Suppose we want to to override authentocation create custom class and and import built in authentication classes in that class we need to overrise authenticate_credentials method declare how to you want to override 

After creating custom class include file path in authentication_classes 

If we want to override authorization class we create custom permission class and import basePermission class and in that class we need to override have_permission method

After writing custom class we need to include custom class path in permission_classes 
